<DocsLayout 
    title="Installation" 
    description="Install RugbyClaw on macOS, Linux, or Windows">
    
    <p class="lead">Install RugbyClaw globally via npm</p>

    <h2>Requirements</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Node.js</strong> 18 or later (<a href="https://nodejs.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">download</a>)</li>
        <li><strong>npm</strong> (included with Node.js)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Install</h2>
    <pre><code>npm install -g rugbyclaw</code></pre>

    <p>This installs RugbyClaw globally so you can run it from anywhere.</p>

    <h2>Verify Installation</h2>
    <pre><code>rugbyclaw --version</code></pre>

    <p>Should output the version number (e.g., <code>0.1.6</code>).</p>

    <h2>Your First Command</h2>
    <pre><code>rugbyclaw start</code></pre>

    <p>Works immediately â€” no configuration required. Default leagues include Top 14, Premiership, URC, Champions Cup, and Six Nations.</p>

    <h2>Platform-Specific Notes</h2>

    <h3>macOS</h3>
    <p>Install via <a href="https://brew.sh" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Homebrew</a> if you prefer:</p>
    <pre><code>brew install node
npm install -g rugbyclaw</code></pre>

    <h3>Linux</h3>
    <p>Use your distribution's package manager to install Node.js first:</p>
    <pre><code># Ubuntu/Debian
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nodejs npm
npm install -g rugbyclaw

# Fedora
sudo dnf install nodejs npm
npm install -g rugbyclaw</code></pre>

    <h3>Windows</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Download and install Node.js from <a href="https://nodejs.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">nodejs.org</a></li>
        <li>Open PowerShell or Command Prompt</li>
        <li>Run: <code>npm install -g rugbyclaw</code></li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Updating</h2>
    <p>Update to the latest version:</p>
    <pre><code>npm update -g rugbyclaw</code></pre>

    <h2>Uninstalling</h2>
    <pre><code>npm uninstall -g rugbyclaw</code></pre>

